  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Several prior works have focused on optimizing dialogue using offline methods applied to static datasets (Jaques et al., 2020; Jang et al., 2022; Snell et al., 2022; Verma et al., 2022; Chen et al., 2025).",
    "Notably, Chen et al. (2025) performs inference-time search on a model trained offline.",
    "In contrast, our approach is designed to support periodic online updates.",
    "This periodic updating not only distinguishes our method from fully offline approaches, but also enables a much simpler algorithmic framework that mirrors the evaluation and improvement steps found in classical policy iteration.",
    "We introduce a novel and real-world multi-turn RL problem where reward signals are truly dependent on the sequencing of long-term interactions."
  ],
